title: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage

! Using JSON Convert

! Opening the Console

Click the {{$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/icon}} icon in the
page-controls toolbar, or navigate directly to
[[the Console|$:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/Console]].

! Importing data

# Paste JSON into the source box, or drop a `.json` file onto the
  textarea (the ''Choose File'' button works too).
# Pick a mapping profile from the dropdown.  Existing profiles are
  any tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/json-convert/mapping`.
# Click ''Convert'' to stage tiddlers without writing them to the
  wiki.
# Review the staged tiddlers ÔÇö each row has ''add'', ''skip'',
  ''overwrite'', or ''rename'' depending on whether the target
  title collides with an existing tiddler.
# Click ''Apply'' to commit, or ''Cancel'' to discard.

! Authoring a mapping profile

Click ''NewÔÇª'' next to the profile dropdown to start an empty
profile, or ''Edit'' to open an existing one.  The editor has:

* ''Records path'' ÔÇö a `{{...}}` path that resolves to the array of
  records.  Each element becomes one tiddler.  Use `{{questions[*]}}`,
  `{{data.items[*]}}`, `{{[*].subgroups[*].items[*]}}`, and so on.
  Click ''BrowseÔÇª'' to pick a path from the parsed sample data.
* ''TiddlyWiki Fields'' ÔÇö bindings for standard fields.  `title` is
  required; `text`, `tags`, `caption` are common.  Click ''Edit'' on
  a row to enter edit mode; ''Done'' collapses it.
* ''Custom Fields'' ÔÇö any additional fields.  Click ''Add'' in the
  Custom Fields header to add a row, then rename it inline.

! Mapping syntax

!! Tokens

Bindings are template strings.  `{{path}}` tokens are replaced with
values resolved against the current record:

```
"{{course}}/{{name}}-{{id}}"
```

Literal text passes through.  Multiple tokens per binding are fine.

!! Per-token transforms

`{{path|name}}` pipes the resolved value through a named transform.
Chain them left-to-right:

```
"{{title|slugify|truncate}}"
```

Transforms shipped with this plugin:

* `html-to-wikitext` ÔÇö currently a pass-through placeholder for
  upcoming HTML ÔåÆ wikitext conversion
* `split-csv` ÔÇö splits a comma-separated string into a TiddlyWiki
  tag list, with `[[ÔÇª]]` quoting around items containing whitespace
* `timestamp-to-date` ÔÇö converts a Unix epoch (seconds or
  milliseconds) into a TiddlyWiki date string
* `to-upper-case`, `to-lower-case`, `to-title-case` ÔÇö case conversion
  via the matching TiddlyWiki filter operators
* `slugify` ÔÇö lowercases, replaces runs of non-alphanumerics with
  `-`, trims dashes from the ends

!! Ancestor scopes

When the records path crosses multiple `[*]` boundaries, the engine
tracks parent scopes.  Bindings can step out of the current scope
with `..`:

```
{
  "records": "{{groups[*].items[*]}}",
  "tw-fields": {
    "title": "{{../group-name}} / {{item-name}}"
  }
}
```

* `{{item-name}}` resolves against the current record (the item).
* `{{../field}}` resolves against the parent scope (the group).
* `{{../../field}}` against the grandparent (the document root).

The Browse modal shows one tree per ancestor scope so you can click
fields instead of typing the `../` prefix.

! Custom transforms

Create a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/json-convert/transform`.  Two body
languages are supported, distinguished by the tiddler's `type`
field.  In both, the input is available as a variable called
`value`.

The transform's profile-facing name comes from the tiddler's `name`
field; if that's absent, it's a slug of the tiddler title.

!! JavaScript

`type: application/javascript`.  The body is a function body that
returns the transformed value:

```
title: Year Bucket
name: year-bucket
tags: $:/tags/json-convert/transform
type: application/javascript

const n = Number(value)
if (!Number.isFinite(n)) return ''
return String(Math.floor(n / 10) * 10) + 's'
```

A `2007` input becomes `2000s`.

!! Wikitext

`type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki`.  The body is wikitext rendered with
`value` in scope; its rendered output is the transformed value.
The four case/slug transforms shipped with this plugin are short
wikitext transforms ÔÇö open them to see the pattern.  For example,
`slugify`:

```
{{{ [<value>lowercase[]regsub:g[[^a-z0-9]+],[-]regsub[^-+|-+$],[]] }}}
```

This chains three filter operators ÔÇö lowercase the input, replace
runs of non-alphanumerics with `-`, then trim leading/trailing `-`s.

Wikitext transforms can use any filter operator, macro, or template
TiddlyWiki has, including any plugins installed alongside this one.

Custom transforms appear in the Browse modal's transform picker
alongside the built-ins.

! Tags this plugin uses

* `$:/tags/json-convert/mapping` ÔÇö marks a tiddler as a mapping
  profile (shown in the Console's profile dropdown).
* `$:/tags/json-convert/transform` ÔÇö marks a tiddler as a custom
  transform.

! Imported tiddler audit log

After each Apply, the Console lists every tiddler written in an
''Imported this session'' section.  The list resets on wiki reload
(it lives in `$:/temp/json-convert/audit-log`, which TiddlyWiki
doesn't persist).  Click any title to navigate to it; ''Clear log''
forgets the list without affecting the wiki contents.

! Reverting profile edits

The editor takes a snapshot of the profile when you open it (in
`$:/temp/json-convert/editor/backup`).  A yellow ''Revert to
backup'' bar appears once a backup exists ÔÇö clicking it restores
the profile to its pre-edit state.  The backup resets on wiki
reload.

